{"title_page": "Justin Warner", "text_new": "{{short description|American chef}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox chef\n| name           = Justin Warner\n| image          =\n| caption        = {{small|Justin Warner}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1984|2|11}}\n| birth_place    = [[Hagerstown, Maryland]], US<ref name=\"herald2\">[http://www.herald-mail.com/news/local/hm-former-hagerstown-native-shines-as-next-food-network-star-20120722,0,2440043.story Hagerstown native shines as next 'Food Network Star' \u2013 herald-mail.com]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref>\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| spouse         = Jessica Hinze (2004\u20132007), Brooke Sweeten (2015\u2013)\n| style          = Fine Dining, Circus Cuisine<ref name=\"doordine\">[http://www.doordinebk.com/welcome/]. Retrieved August 17, 2015.</ref>\n| education      = \n| ratings        = <!-- {{plainlist|\n}} -->\n| restaurants = Do or Dine (closed); [[Bedford\u2013Stuyvesant, Brooklyn|Bed-Stuy, Brooklyn, New York]]\n| prevrests      = <!-- {{plainlist|\n}} -->\n| television     = ''Rebel Eats'' (2013)\n| awards         = [[Michelin Guide#Bib Gourmand|Michelin Bib Gourmand]] \n| website        = https://www.facebook.com/EatFellowHumans\nhttp://www.twitch.tv/ChefShock\n}}\n'''Justin M. Warner''' (born February 11, 1984)<ref name=\"herald2\"/><ref name=\"officialtwitter\">[https://twitter.com/EatFellowHumans Justin M. Warner (EatFellowHumans) on Twitter]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"ibtimes\">[http://www.ibtimes.com/next-food-network-star-justin-warner-wins-season-8-befittingly-voting-system-needs-axe-730368 The Next Food Network Star: Justin Warner Wins Season 8 Befittingly, But The Voting System Needs The Axe]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> is an American chef. He is best known for his appearances on [[Food Network]], including the [[Food Network Star (season 8)|eighth season]] of the series ''[[Food Network Star]],'' which he won. He is the author of ''The Laws of Cooking: And How to Break Them'' (2015). He is also the chef host of Eat the Universe on marvel.com where he makes meals inspired by characters of the Marvel Universe.\n\n== Early life ==\nWarner was born on February 11, 1984<ref name=\"birthday\">[https://www.facebook.com/EatFellowHumans/posts/338075989644652 Justin Warner Birthday Announcement on Facebook]</ref> in [[Hagerstown, Maryland]]. His mother, Jan, is a [[teacher|schoolteacher]],<ref name=\"herald2\" /> and his father was a psychiatrist. Warner was born when his father was 57 years old.<ref name=\"knox\">[http://www.knoxnews.com/news/2012/jul/23/justin-warner-winner-food-network-star Justin Warner named winner of 'Food Network Star' competition \u00bb Knoxville News Sentinel]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> In 1998 he was a finalist in the [[Scripps National Spelling Bee|National Spelling Bee]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2012/05/31/living/spelling-bee-experience/index.html|title=The agony and ecstasy of the National Spelling Bee|first=Kat |last=Kinsman|website=CNN|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> His father died shortly after Justin graduated from [[South Hagerstown High School]] in 2002.\n\nWarner has had [[autodidacticism|no formal culinary training]];<ref name=\"foodnetwork\">[http://www.foodnetwork.com/shows/justin-warner/index.html Justin Warner : Shows : Food Network] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020001237/http://www.foodnetwork.com/shows/justin-warner/index.html |date=October 20, 2012 }}. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"herald1\">[http://articles.herald-mail.com/2012-07-17/news/32718320_1_food-network-contestants-team-giada/2 Justin Warner closes in on victory with 'The Next Food Network Star' \u2013 Page 2 \u2013 Herald-Mail]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref> he was inspired to learn to cook by his father.<ref name=\"knox\" />\n\n==Food Network==\nWarner appeared on ''[[24 Hour Restaurant Battle]]'' in August 2010 with his then-girlfriend J.J. Pyle.<ref name=\"mcall\"/><ref name=\"villagevoice\">[http://blogs.villagevoice.com/forkintheroad/2011/09/do_or_dines_jus_1.php Do or Dine's Justin Warner On Why Brunch Sucks: Interview Part 2 \u2013 New York \u2013 Restaurants and Dining \u2013 Fork in the Road]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"eater\">[http://eater.com/archives/2010/07/06/24hour-restaurant-battle-is-like-this-show-and-that-show-and-that-one-too.php 24-Hour Restaurant Battle Sort of Looks Like This Show and That Show and That One, Too \u2013 TV Watch \u2013 Eater National]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> They won the episode with their [[brunch]] restaurant concept,<ref name=\"villagevoice\"/> but the restaurant itself never came to fruition.\n\n===''Food Network Star''===\nLater in 2012 Warner became a contestant on the [[Food Network Star (season 8)|eighth season]] of ''[[Food Network Star]]'', mentored by [[Alton Brown]].<ref name=\"foodnetwork\"/> He did not watch the series before becoming a contestant, because he does not own a television.<ref name=\"mcall\">[http://www.mcall.com/lifestyle/hm-hagerstown-native-justin-warner-competes-on-the-next-food-network-star-20120508,0,4055938.story?page=1 Hagerstown native Justin Warner competes on 'The Next Food Network Star' \u2013 mcall.com]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref> He eventually became one of the final four contestants, and he filmed a pilot for a potential series called ''Rebel with a Culinary Cause''. He won the competition.<ref name=\"ibtimes\"/><ref name=\"blackbook\">[http://www.blackbookmag.com/restaurants/do-or-dine-s-justin-warner-wins-food-network-star-1.51047 Do or Dine's Justin Warner Wins 'Food Network Star' \u2013 Restaurants \u2013 Blackbook] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615205834/http://www.blackbookmag.com/restaurants/do-or-dine-s-justin-warner-wins-food-network-star-1.51047 |date=June 15, 2013 }}. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"rickey\">[http://www.rickey.org/interview-with-justin-warner-food-network-star-season-8-winner Justin Warner \u2013 Food Network Star Season 8 Winner \u2013 Interview | Rickey.org] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130415170119/http://www.rickey.org/interview-with-justin-warner-food-network-star-season-8-winner |date=April 15, 2013 }}. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"knox\"/>\nAlton Brown announced on January 4, 2013, that he will \"regrettably\" not be producing Justin's show.<ref name=\"AB\">[http://www.thebraiser.com/alton-brown-pulls-out-of-justin-warner-show/]. Retrieved January 4, 2013</ref>\nIn March 2013, Justin Warner debuted a one-hour pilot special on Food Network titled ''Rebel Eats''. In 2014, he was a judge on ''[[Guy's Grocery Games]]''.{{Citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n== Career ==\nHe was one of the co-owners of Do or Dine restaurant in [[Bedford\u2013Stuyvesant, Brooklyn|Bed-Stuy, New York]], before it closed in September 2015.<ref name=\"blackbook\" /><ref name=\"brooklynink\">[http://thebrooklynink.com/2012/01/16/40276-fun-with-food-how-do-or-dine-does-it Do or Dine, Brooklyn Restaurant | Local Brooklyn News and Features | The Brooklyn Ink]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> \n\nStarting October 31, 2016 Warner, along with a few others acting as staff, created a new cooking show on Twitch.tv known as Chefshock, \"Shockingly Real, Shockingly Live, and just plain Shockingly Delicious.\", where he cooks live from his home kitchen from completely raw ingredients with viewers encouraged to cook along and ask questions.<ref>[https://www.twitch.tv/chefshock Justin Warner's Twitch Livestream Cooking Show]</ref> Questions are often presented to Warner by a moderator who shares in eating the finished results, while those that cook along and post their own progress pictures are featured throughout the show during lulls in the cooking process. Ingredients required to cook along at home are shared a week in advance, usually through the use of google documents to allow those that wish to participate time to gather them.<ref>[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QUKu9oaIAkifFQ3LLxGaZSsNCTtQy50wnStLo25f5ec/edit Chefshock Ingredients Document List]</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn June 29, 2015, Justin Warner married his fianc\u00e9e Brooke Sweeten.<ref>[http://www.foodnetworkgossip.com/2015/06/justin-warner-got-married-today.html Justin Warner Got Married Today | Food Network Gossip]. Retrieved August 19, 2015.</ref> \n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=4 style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Television\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Year\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Series\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Role\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[24 Hour Restaurant Battle]]''\n|Himself\n|Episode winner with partner J.J.\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2012\n| ''[[Food Network Star]]''\n| Himself\n| Contestant: [[Food Network Star (season 8)|Season 8]]\n|-\n| ''Unique Eats''\n| Himself\n| Season 4 episode 7: \"Comfort Food\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Rebel Eats''\n| Himself/Host\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Unique Sweets''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n| 2014\u2013present\n| ''[[Guy's Grocery Games]]''\n| Himself\n| Recurring judge<br/> Has competed on the show.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[Kitchen Nightmares]]''\n| Himself\n| Competitor\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Breaking the Rules: Chocolate''\n| Himself/Host\n| \"Superstar Sabatoge\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Cutthroat Kitchen]]''\n| Himself\n| Competitor\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''Guilty Pleasures''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n| ''ChefShock''\n| Himself/Co-host\n| Writer and producer for the show\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Cook vs. Cons''\n| Himself\n| Recurring judge\n|}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* ''The Laws of Cooking: And How to Break Them'' ({{ISBN|1-25006-513-5}}, 2015)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|http://www.eatfellowhumans.com/}}\n*{{Facebook|EatFellowHumans|Justin Warner}}\n*{{Twitter}}\n\n{{Food Network Star}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Warner, Justin}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:American television chefs]]\n[[Category:Male chefs]]\n[[Category:Food Network chefs]]\n[[Category:Food Network Star winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hagerstown, Maryland]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American chef}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox chef\n| name           = Justin Warner\n| image          =\n| caption        = {{small|Justin Warner}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1984|2|11}}\n| birth_place    = [[Hagerstown, Maryland]], US<ref name=\"herald2\">[http://www.herald-mail.com/news/local/hm-former-hagerstown-native-shines-as-next-food-network-star-20120722,0,2440043.story Hagerstown native shines as next 'Food Network Star' \u2013 herald-mail.com]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref>\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| spouse         = Jessica Hinze (2004\u20132007), Brooke Sweeten (2015\u2013)\n| style          = Fine Dining, Circus Cuisine<ref name=\"doordine\">[http://www.doordinebk.com/welcome/]. Retrieved August 17, 2015.</ref>\n| education      = \n| ratings        = <!-- {{plainlist|\n}} -->\n| restaurants = Do or Dine (closed); [[Bedford\u2013Stuyvesant, Brooklyn|Bed-Stuy, Brooklyn, New York]]\n| prevrests      = <!-- {{plainlist|\n}} -->\n| television     = ''Rebel Eats'' (2013)\n| awards         = [[Michelin Guide#Bib Gourmand|Michelin Bib Gourmand]] \n| website        = https://www.facebook.com/EatFellowHumans\nhttp://www.twitch.tv/ChefShock\n}}\n'''Justin M. Warner''' (born February 11, 1984)<ref name=\"herald2\"/><ref name=\"officialtwitter\">[https://twitter.com/EatFellowHumans Justin M. Warner (EatFellowHumans) on Twitter]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"ibtimes\">[http://www.ibtimes.com/next-food-network-star-justin-warner-wins-season-8-befittingly-voting-system-needs-axe-730368 The Next Food Network Star: Justin Warner Wins Season 8 Befittingly, But The Voting System Needs The Axe]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> is an American chef. He is best known for his appearances on [[Food Network]], including the [[Food Network Star (season 8)|eighth season]] of the series ''[[Food Network Star]],'' which he won. He is the author of ''The Laws of Cooking: And How to Break Them'' (2015). He is also the chef host of Eat the Universe on marvel.com where he makes meals inspired by characters of the Marvel Universe.\n\n== Early life ==\nWarner was born on February 11, 1984<ref name=\"birthday\">[https://www.facebook.com/EatFellowHumans/posts/338075989644652 Justin Warner Birthday Announcement on Facebook]</ref> in [[Hagerstown, Maryland]]. His mother, Jan, is a [[teacher|schoolteacher]],<ref name=\"herald2\" /> and his father was a psychiatrist. Warner was born when his father was 57 years old.<ref name=\"knox\">[http://www.knoxnews.com/news/2012/jul/23/justin-warner-winner-food-network-star Justin Warner named winner of 'Food Network Star' competition \u00bb Knoxville News Sentinel]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> In 1998 he was a finalist in the [[Scripps National Spelling Bee|National Spelling Bee]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2012/05/31/living/spelling-bee-experience/index.html|title=The agony and ecstasy of the National Spelling Bee|last=CNN|first=By Kat Kinsman|website=CNN|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref> His father died shortly after Justin graduated from [[South Hagerstown High School]] in 2002.\n\nWarner has had [[autodidacticism|no formal culinary training]];<ref name=\"foodnetwork\">[http://www.foodnetwork.com/shows/justin-warner/index.html Justin Warner : Shows : Food Network] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020001237/http://www.foodnetwork.com/shows/justin-warner/index.html |date=October 20, 2012 }}. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"herald1\">[http://articles.herald-mail.com/2012-07-17/news/32718320_1_food-network-contestants-team-giada/2 Justin Warner closes in on victory with 'The Next Food Network Star' \u2013 Page 2 \u2013 Herald-Mail]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref> he was inspired to learn to cook by his father.<ref name=\"knox\" />\n\n==Food Network==\nWarner appeared on ''[[24 Hour Restaurant Battle]]'' in August 2010 with his then-girlfriend J.J. Pyle.<ref name=\"mcall\"/><ref name=\"villagevoice\">[http://blogs.villagevoice.com/forkintheroad/2011/09/do_or_dines_jus_1.php Do or Dine's Justin Warner On Why Brunch Sucks: Interview Part 2 \u2013 New York \u2013 Restaurants and Dining \u2013 Fork in the Road]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"eater\">[http://eater.com/archives/2010/07/06/24hour-restaurant-battle-is-like-this-show-and-that-show-and-that-one-too.php 24-Hour Restaurant Battle Sort of Looks Like This Show and That Show and That One, Too \u2013 TV Watch \u2013 Eater National]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> They won the episode with their [[brunch]] restaurant concept,<ref name=\"villagevoice\"/> but the restaurant itself never came to fruition.\n\n===''Food Network Star''===\nLater in 2012 Warner became a contestant on the [[Food Network Star (season 8)|eighth season]] of ''[[Food Network Star]]'', mentored by [[Alton Brown]].<ref name=\"foodnetwork\"/> He did not watch the series before becoming a contestant, because he does not own a television.<ref name=\"mcall\">[http://www.mcall.com/lifestyle/hm-hagerstown-native-justin-warner-competes-on-the-next-food-network-star-20120508,0,4055938.story?page=1 Hagerstown native Justin Warner competes on 'The Next Food Network Star' \u2013 mcall.com]. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref> He eventually became one of the final four contestants, and he filmed a pilot for a potential series called ''Rebel with a Culinary Cause''. He won the competition.<ref name=\"ibtimes\"/><ref name=\"blackbook\">[http://www.blackbookmag.com/restaurants/do-or-dine-s-justin-warner-wins-food-network-star-1.51047 Do or Dine's Justin Warner Wins 'Food Network Star' \u2013 Restaurants \u2013 Blackbook] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130615205834/http://www.blackbookmag.com/restaurants/do-or-dine-s-justin-warner-wins-food-network-star-1.51047 |date=June 15, 2013 }}. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"rickey\">[http://www.rickey.org/interview-with-justin-warner-food-network-star-season-8-winner Justin Warner \u2013 Food Network Star Season 8 Winner \u2013 Interview | Rickey.org] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130415170119/http://www.rickey.org/interview-with-justin-warner-food-network-star-season-8-winner |date=April 15, 2013 }}. Retrieved October 3, 2012.</ref><ref name=\"knox\"/>\nAlton Brown announced on January 4, 2013, that he will \"regrettably\" not be producing Justin's show.<ref name=\"AB\">[http://www.thebraiser.com/alton-brown-pulls-out-of-justin-warner-show/]. Retrieved January 4, 2013</ref>\nIn March 2013, Justin Warner debuted a one-hour pilot special on Food Network titled ''Rebel Eats''. In 2014, he was a judge on ''[[Guy's Grocery Games]]''.{{Citation needed|date=July 2019}}\n\n== Career ==\nHe was one of the co-owners of Do or Dine restaurant in [[Bedford\u2013Stuyvesant, Brooklyn|Bed-Stuy, New York]], before it closed in September 2015.<ref name=\"blackbook\" /><ref name=\"brooklynink\">[http://thebrooklynink.com/2012/01/16/40276-fun-with-food-how-do-or-dine-does-it Do or Dine, Brooklyn Restaurant | Local Brooklyn News and Features | The Brooklyn Ink]. Retrieved October 4, 2012.</ref> \n\nStarting October 31, 2016 Warner, along with a few others acting as staff, created a new cooking show on Twitch.tv known as Chefshock, \"Shockingly Real, Shockingly Live, and just plain Shockingly Delicious.\", where he cooks live from his home kitchen from completely raw ingredients with viewers encouraged to cook along and ask questions.<ref>[https://www.twitch.tv/chefshock Justin Warner's Twitch Livestream Cooking Show]</ref> Questions are often presented to Warner by a moderator who shares in eating the finished results, while those that cook along and post their own progress pictures are featured throughout the show during lulls in the cooking process. Ingredients required to cook along at home are shared a week in advance, usually through the use of google documents to allow those that wish to participate time to gather them.<ref>[https://docs.google.com/document/d/1QUKu9oaIAkifFQ3LLxGaZSsNCTtQy50wnStLo25f5ec/edit Chefshock Ingredients Document List]</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn June 29, 2015, Justin Warner married his fianc\u00e9e Brooke Sweeten.<ref>[http://www.foodnetworkgossip.com/2015/06/justin-warner-got-married-today.html Justin Warner Got Married Today | Food Network Gossip]. Retrieved August 19, 2015.</ref> \n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=4 style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\" | Television\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Year\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Series\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Role\n! style=\"background:#ccc;\"| Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[24 Hour Restaurant Battle]]''\n|Himself\n|Episode winner with partner J.J.\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2012\n| ''[[Food Network Star]]''\n| Himself\n| Contestant: [[Food Network Star (season 8)|Season 8]]\n|-\n| ''Unique Eats''\n| Himself\n| Season 4 episode 7: \"Comfort Food\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Rebel Eats''\n| Himself/Host\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Unique Sweets''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n| 2014\u2013present\n| ''[[Guy's Grocery Games]]''\n| Himself\n| Recurring judge<br/> Has competed on the show.\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[Kitchen Nightmares]]''\n| Himself\n| Competitor\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Breaking the Rules: Chocolate''\n| Himself/Host\n| \"Superstar Sabatoge\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Cutthroat Kitchen]]''\n| Himself\n| Competitor\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''Guilty Pleasures''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n| 2016\u2013present\n| ''ChefShock''\n| Himself/Co-host\n| Writer and producer for the show\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''Cook vs. Cons''\n| Himself\n